Redux thunk acts as middleware which allows an individual to write action creators that return functions instead of actions. This is also used as a delay function in order to delay dispatch of an action if a certain condition is met. The two store methods _getState()_ and _dispatch()_ are provided as parameters to the inner function.

In order to activate Redux thunk, we must first use applyMiddleware() method as shown below:

    import{ createStore, applyMiddleware } from 'redux';
    import thunk from 'redux-thunk';
    import rootReducer from './reducers/index';

    //Note: this API requires redux@>=3.1.0

    const store= createStore(
         rootReducer,
         applyMiddleware(thunk)
    );

